The paper deals with the definition of a notion of bisimulation for state-to-function transition systems (FuTS), which are a generalization of labeled transition systems and quantitative semantical models. This topic is relevant to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), formal languages and automata theory (cs.LT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
